{"lemma":"سارٍ","slug":"سارٍ","root":"س.ر.#","root_slug":"س-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سارٍ","root":"سير","pos":"V","occurrence_count":16},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18568","n19437","n19685","n21203","n21410","n21415"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18568","headword_ar":"سَاَرَ","root":"sA^r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say^ira","text_ar":"سَيِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suw^orN","text_ar":"سُوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It remained; became left, as a residue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n19437","headword_ar":"سَارٌّ","root":"sr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sar~N","text_ar":"سَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19685","headword_ar":"سَارٍ","root":"srY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Journeying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelling, by night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the night, in a general sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA: *) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suraApN","text_ar":"سُرَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, because of his going [about] by night, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAriY","text_ar":"السَّارِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmusaAriY","text_ar":"المُسَارِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmusotariY","text_ar":"المُسْتَرِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21203","headword_ar":"سَارَ","root":"swr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasuwru","text_ar":"يَسُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suw^uwrN","text_ar":"سُوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworN","text_ar":"سَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or both, (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworapN","text_ar":"سَوْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) [but this last is an inf. n. of un.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprang,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprang,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"committed an assault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon another,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like as he does who behaves in an annoying manner towards his cup-companion in his intoxication."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also 3.]) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra Al$~araAbu fiY raA^osihi","text_ar":"سَارَ الشَّرَابُ فِى رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworN","text_ar":"سَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suw^uwrN","text_ar":"سُوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwuwrN","text_ar":"سُوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with the root, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwaArN","text_ar":"سُوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wine assaulted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rushed into, his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wine circulated in his head, and rose into it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra Al$~araAbu","text_ar":"سَارَ الشَّرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworN","text_ar":"سَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworapN","text_ar":"سَوْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wine had an overpowering influence upon the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saArato fiyhi Humay~aA AlkaA^osi","text_ar":"سَارَتْ فِيهِ حُمَيَّا الكَاْسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the force"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overpowering influence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworap","text_ar":"سَوْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fumes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the cup of wine mounted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose, to his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmY","text_ar":"حمى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr","text_ar":"سار"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was angry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr","text_ar":"سار"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworN","text_ar":"سَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became elevated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"surotu A_ilayohi fiY A^aEaAliY Als~uwri"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rose to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, parts of the wall"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the city or town &c.]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And one says to a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surosuro","text_ar":"سُرْسُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rise thou, rise thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to eminence,] in enjoining aspiration to the means of acquiring eminence, or nobility: (IAar, K, * TA:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surotu AlHaAy^iTa","text_ar":"سُرْتُ الحَايِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ascended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mounted, upon the wall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  See also 5, in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrabihi","text_ar":"سُورَبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"syr","text_ar":"سير"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Mgh","A","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n21410","headword_ar":"سَارَ","root":"syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasiyru","text_ar":"يَسِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorN","text_ar":"سَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrN","text_ar":"مَسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) which latter is extr., for by rule it should be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEalN","text_ar":"مَفْعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrapN","text_ar":"مَسِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayoruwrapN","text_ar":"سَيْرُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoluwlapN","text_ar":"قَيْلُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but [Mtr says] we have not heard it, (Mgh,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoyaArN","text_ar":"تَسْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) which last denotes repetition or frequency of the action, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, went"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any pace"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed, along; marched, journeyed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proceeded; went away, passed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by night"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saArati Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"سَارَتِ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beast went, went along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr sayorFA $adiydFA","text_ar":"سار سَيْرًا شَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel or other beast, and a man,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went a vehement pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr AlEanaqa","text_ar":"سار العَنَقَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel, or a horse,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went the pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the manner, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanaq","text_ar":"العَنَق"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the like.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAruwA","text_ar":"سَارُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino baladK libaladK","text_ar":"مِنْ بَلَدٍ لِبَلَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeyed, from town to town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from country to country"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr mino baladK A_ilaY baladK","text_ar":"سار مِنْ بَلَدٍ اـِلَى بَلَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAraka A@ll~`hu fiY masiyrika","text_ar":"بَارَكَ ا@للّٰهُ فِى مَسِيرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorika","text_ar":"سَيْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God bless thy journeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro Eanoka","text_ar":"سِرْ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou from thy place; pass thou from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nf*","text_ar":"نفذ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feign thou heedlessness, and bear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be forbearing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"an elliptical phrase; as though it were originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro wadaEo Eanoka AlmiraA='a","text_ar":"سِرْ وَدَعْ عَنْكَ المِرَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAl$~ak~a","text_ar":"وَالشَّكَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go thou, and leave wrangling and doubt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sArt Als~afiynapu","text_ar":"سارت السَّفِينَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ship went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sailed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayoru Als~afiynapi","text_ar":"سَيْرُ السَّفِينَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a tropical phrase. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr siyrapF HasanapF","text_ar":"سار سِيرَةً حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued a good way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, A, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyrapF","text_ar":"سِيرَةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyHapF","text_ar":"قَبِيحَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bad way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr fiY","text_ar":"سار فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became current,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commonly known, among the people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasay~ara","text_ar":"تَسَيَّرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone; (see Har p. 318;)] i. e. a proverb, and a saying. (M.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sArt sun~apN","text_ar":"سارت سُنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, obtained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was usual, among people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr","text_ar":"سار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also trans.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~ara","text_ar":"سَيَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, Msb, K.) See the latter, in five places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr","text_ar":"سار"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sun~apF","text_ar":"سُنَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused, a way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, to obtain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became usual, among people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * TA.) The Hudhalee (Khálid Ibn-Zuheyr, M) says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falaA tajozaEano mino sun~apK A^anota sirotahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        faA^aw~alu raADK sun~apF mano yasiyruhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then by no means be thou impatient of a way of acting which thou hast made usual; for the first who should be content with a way of acting is he who makes it usual"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M, L, TA: but in the M and TA, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tjzEn","text_ar":"تجزعن"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagoDabano","text_ar":"تَغْضَبَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21415","headword_ar":"سَارٌ","root":"syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^irN","text_ar":"سَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"سار","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_31","lexicon_en":"Al-Rāghib al-Isfahānī, al-Mufradāt fī Gharīb al-Qurʾān (d. c. 1109 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المفردات في غريب القرآن للراغب الأصفهاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=61774#fc9e74","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">سار</span><br><span>السَّيْرُ: المضيّ في الأرض، ورجل سَائِرٌ، وسَيَّارٌ، والسَّيَّارَةُ: الجماعة، قال تعالى:</span><br><span>وَجاءَتْ سَيَّارَةٌ</span><br><span>[يوسف/ 19] ، يقال:</span><br><span>سِرْتُ، وسِرْتُ بفلان، وسِرْتُهُ أيضا، وسَيَّرْتُهُ على التّكثير، فمن الأوّل قوله: أَفَلَمْ يَسِيرُوا</span><br><span>[الحج/ 46] ، قُلْ سِيرُوا</span><br><span>[الأنعام/ 11] ، سِيرُوا فِيها لَيالِيَ [سبأ/ 18] ، ومن الثاني قوله: سارَ بِأَهْلِهِ</span><br><span>[القصص/ 29] ، ولم يجئ في القرآن القسم الثالث، وهو سِرْتُهُ.</span><br><span>والرابع قوله: وَسُيِّرَتِ الْجِبالُ</span><br><span>[النبأ/ 20] ، هُوَ الَّذِي يُسَيِّرُكُمْ فِي الْبَرِّ وَالْبَحْرِ</span><br><span>[يونس/ 22] ، وأمّا قوله: سِيرُوا فِي الْأَرْضِ</span><br><span>[النمل/ 69] فقد قيل: حثّ على السّياحة في الأرض بالجسم، وقيل: حثّ على إجالة الفكر، ومراعاة أحواله كما روي في الخبر أنه قيل في وصف الأولياء: (أبدانهم في الأرض سَائِرَةٌ وقلوبهم في الملكوت جائلة) ، ومنهم من حمل ذلك على الجدّ في العبادة المتوصّل بها إلى الثواب، وعلى ذلك حمل قوله عليه السلام: «سافروا تغنموا» ، والتَّسْيِيرُ ضربان:</span><br><span>أحدهما: بالأمر، والاختيار، والإرادة من السائر نحو: هُوَ الَّذِي يُسَيِّرُكُمْ [يونس/ 22] .</span><br><span>والثاني: بالقهر والتّسخير كتسخير الجبال وَإِذَا الْجِبالُ سُيِّرَتْ [التكوير/ 3] ، وقوله:</span><br><span>وَسُيِّرَتِ الْجِبالُ [النبأ/ 20] ، والسِّيرَةُ: الحالة التي يكون عليها الإنسان وغيره، غريزيّا كان أو مكتسبا، يقال: فلان له سيرة حسنة، وسيرة قبيحة، وقوله: سَنُعِيدُها سِيرَتَهَا الْأُولى [طه/ 21] ، أي: الحالة التي كانت عليها من كونها عودا.</span>"}]}}